	        		        	<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Climateliteracy:DataPortals</h1>
				<div id="bodyContent">
		            <h3 id="siteSub">From Coursera</h3>
		            <div id="contentSub"></div>
		            		            		            					<!-- start content -->
					<div lang="en" dir="ltr" class="mw-content-ltr"><p>Back to the <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://share.coursera.org/wiki/index.php/Climateliteracy:Main">Climate Literacy Main Wiki Page</a></p>
<p>This page is meant to be a place to collect links to data portals where you can download and analyze climate data yourself.  There is a ton of data freely available to you.  Some of the portals are fairly complex; others provide pretty easy access.  Feel free to add to this page, and please include a description.  </p>
<p><strong>LIST OF OPEN-ACCESS DATA SOURCES</strong></p>
<ul>
<li><p><strong><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.esrl.noaa.gov/gmd/ccgg/trends/#mlo_data">Atmospheric CO2 data from Mauna Loa (Earth System Research Laboratory)</a></strong>  On this page are links to the atmospheric CO2 data measured at Mauna Loa, Hawaii, since the late 1950s.  </p></li>
<li><p><strong><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://data.giss.nasa.gov/gistemp/#tabledata">Temperature anomaly data from NASA-GISS</a></strong>
On this page are links to global, hemispheric, and latitudinal temperature measurements compiled by NASA-GISS.</p></li>
<li><p><strong><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/paleo/wdc-paleo.html">World Data Center for Paleoclimatology</a></strong>
This is the main page for this database with lots of freely available paleoclimate data.  Click "Data" on the bar near the top to get a list of what's available.  Here are some more specific links:</p></li>
<li><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="ftp://ftp.ncdc.noaa.gov/pub/data/paleo/contributions_by_author/zachos2001/zachos2001.txt">Cenozoic Global Deep-Sea Stable Isotope Data</a> from Zachos et al., 2001</p></li>
<li><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="ftp://ftp.ncdc.noaa.gov/pub/data/paleo/icecore/antarctica/epica_domec/edc-co2-2008.txt">CO2 data from Antarctic Ice Cores</a> from EPICA (data from various references combined - this one is from Luthi et al., 2008)</p></li>
<li><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.archive.arm.gov">Atmospheric Radiation Measurement Program</a> Radiation, Aerosol, Cloud Property, Surface Data for certain sites up to 20 years.</p></li>
<li><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://data.worldbank.org/climate-change">The World Bank: Open Data Resources For Climate Change</a></p></li>
<li><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.icsu-wds.org/services/data-portal">International Council of Science (ICSU) World Data System (WDS)</a></p></li>
<li><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.ncdc.noaa.gov/oa/wdc/index.php">World Data Center (WDC) for Meteorology - Asheville</a> Maintained as the U.S. National Climatic Data Center (NCDC) by the U.S. National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration (NOAA).</p></li>
<li><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://nsidc.org/data/search/data-search.html">World Data Center (WDC) for Glaciology - Boulder</a>  Cryosphere data - joint partnership of the University of Colorado, Cooperative Institute for Research in Environmental Sciences (CIRES), and the National Oceanic Atmospheric Administration (NOAA). The WDC for Glaciology, Boulder (WDC-Glaciology Boulder) is collocated with the National Snow and Ice Data Center (NSIDC).</p></li>
<li><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://climatedataguide.ucar.edu/">Climate Data Guide</a> A database of 145 data sets covering various aspects of climate science.</p></li>
<li><p><a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://mynasadata.larc.nasa.gov/">My NASA Data</a> A tool to view NASA satellite data using easily understandable graphics.</p></li>
</ul>

